snippet.textDisplay:
The "Deadly SARS outbreak" killed 774 people (2002-2003), Ebola killed11,325 (2014-2016), and this latest virus, 2019-ncov, has killed 259 (1 February 2020). In comparison, influenza has killed 10,000 people in the US alone this season, including 68 children, and hospitalizing another 150,000. Before it's all said and done, the flu could kill half a million people worldwide before it's done!
The thing is, influenza deaths are largely preventable. A flu shot & hand washing help keep you from getting the flu, and staying home & away from others helps the keep the unlucky from spreading the misery.
Let's use a little common sense and do what we can to minimize all these viral threats
